   <mods:abstract>Although Jay leaves for Paris, Littlepage must remain in Madrid since he
            does not have funds to accompany Jay. Littlepage will return to America next March if
            Lewis' "surprising and unaccountable silence still continues." Two and one-half years
            have passed since Littlepage left America, and he has heard nothing from any of his
            friends in America, and he has heard nothing from any of his friends in America. Tells
            of his experience in Spain and with the Duke de Crillon. He will have to abandon all of
            his hopes for a career in politics if Lewis does not respond. He will send 12 different
            copies of this letter to Lewis.</mods:abstract>
